result.title: 1988 - 1988 Centre for Environment, Fisheries & Aquaculture Science (Cefas) Survey : SUZA 1/88 (part of English Channel Beam Trawl Survey (VIId and IVc), Qtr 3 (FSS: BTS7D))
result.name: 1988-1988-centre-for-environment-fisheries-aquaculture-science-cefas-survey-suza-1-88-part-of-e
result.notes:
This survey was undertaken by Cefas as part of the English Channel Beam Trawl 
Survey (VIId and IVc), Qtr 3 (FSS: BTS7D);

Station, catch, length (all species) and biological data (selected species) 
for each of the annual surveys covering the Southern North Sea and Eastern 
English Channel using research vessels and 4m beam trawl in support of EU data 
regulations and as part of an ICES funded research program. Additional aims 
include collection of benthic, litter, water temperature and salinity and 
acoustic data.

Survey took place between 09/08/1988 and 19/08/1988 on Suzanna D

Equipment used during this survey :


-   Beam trawl 4m steel liner only catch linked to 101530101
-   Beam Trawl 4m steel commercial 3/5 link mat flip up 40mm Double beam

Survey operations were undertaken on 51 stations

57 different species were caught on this survey
